-- China State Researcher Warns of `Hot Money' After Rate Increase, CCTV Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-10-19T23:26:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-19/china-state-researcher-warns-of-hot-money-after-rate-increase-cctv-says.html
China needs to take greater effort
to manage “hot money” inflows after increasing interest rates,
China Central Television reported, citing Ba Shusong, deputy
head of the financial institute of the State Council’s
Development Research Center.  The rate increases can help rein in property bubbles in the
country, the report said, citing Ba.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
